ENTRY            30081   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30081001   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 12         36
TITLE      Angular distribution of gamma rays from inelastic
            scattering of 14.1 MeV neutrons on 12C and 16O
AUTHOR     (T.Kozlowski, W.Kusch, J.Wojtkowska)
INSTITUTE  (3POLIPJ)
REFERENCE  (R,INR-661,1965)
           discussion, curves, no data tables curves have wrong
            cos(theta) scale
INC-SOURCE (D-T) the reaction T(d,n)He4 was used
DETECTOR   (SCIN) The alpha particles defining the cone of
            14.1 MeV neutrons were detected with scintillation
            counter. Gamma rays from samples were detected with a
            2.5 cm diameter and 5cm long NaI-scintillation counter
            placed at 13 cm from the sample.
METHOD     (COINC) The coincidence circuit between alpha and gamma
            detectors with time resolution of 70 ns gated 400
            channel pulse height analyzer, which recorded the
            gamma rays spectra.
MONITOR    (6-C-12(N,INL)6-C-12,PAR,SIG)
            Normalized to the total sigma
            For excitation of the 4.43 MeV state in 12C.
CORRECTION The cross-sections determined have been corrected for
           the following effects=
            .Attenuation of incident neutron beam in the sample
            .Attenuation of gamma rays in the sample
            .Angular spread of gamma rays
            .Relative detection efficiency of gamma rays for
             double escape peak
           In the calculation of these corrections the measured
            profile of neutron beam was taken into account.
           The multiple scattering corrections were only estimated
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,T.Kozlowski+,R,INR-661,1965)
             data from Kozlowski (letter of 17Feb1967)
HISTORY    (19720105T) converted from Dastar to Exfor
           (20080305A) BIB section updated
           (20260407A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              36
